			<!-- icon and title -->
			<div class="smallfont">
				<img class="inlineimg" src="images/icons/icon1.gif" alt="Default" border="0" />
				<strong>10th Ring Questions</strong>
			</div>
			<hr size="1" style="color:#000000" />
			<!-- / icon and title -->
		
		
		<!-- message -->
		<div>I'd been gearing towards replacing the functionality of my War Crested Ring (ID4) with Anger of Druzzil / ID2 augs via LDoN so I can get a higher hp ring.  I'm not ST/VT/elem geared and in a small family guild.<br />
<br />
The 10th ring has always been looked upon by myself as unattainable; likely as I recall the early days on Prexus when we had 70 - 100 peeps on the ringwars and still failed.  And since the day of the very first successful 10th ring on the server (after a half dozen tries); I've only helped once or twice in subsequent rings and so I'm out of touch on what it takes nowadays.<br />
<br />
I have two questions:<br />
<br />
1) Are there still stacking issues with dru/shm regen and some atk buffs?  I suppose that even if there are, one could just run out and get an 8th ring to use as DS/clicky instead of the effect on the 10th if it's overwritten.<br />
<br />
2) Does the person doing the final ring turn-in (9th ring + head) have to be the one who initiated the war?  Let me clarify: we are short on tankage (our guild + small alliance) where we probably can't afford to have me standing back with the seneschal doing nothing.  Two of us have our 9th rings and plan to do the 10th; so if the other person (a BL) turns in his 9th ring/dirk etc to initiate the war and control the hero's etc. (allowing me to run around and tank waves, etc.), can I loot Narandi's head and do the final turn ins for the 10th ring?  If so, that means the BL can do the turn in next time and loot the head for his turn in.  Would this work?<br />
<br />
I realize the 10th ring isn't terribly uber these days, and that the ringwar is trivial for elem-geared guilds but this is prolly as good as I'll get for a finger slot.  I figure we can come up with at least 24 peeps -- avg lvl 64, hopefully 30 or so but will be light on tanks.  Doable?</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		<!-- sig -->
