		<!-- message -->
		<div>Klotar, we do this with 30ish all the time.   No VT, no EP gear.<br />
<br />
Have a good snare group of druids and rangers.  Festering works well also.  It is nice to have a couple chanters to tash the 3rd wave.  They are very MR and tash will help snares land.  I also use AoD on the third wave, every bit helps.  Get everything snared ASAP.  Mobs are easy to tank, the only problem is letting them run free.<br />
<br />
If you have two bards with the gate song, you are guaranteed success.  Just have them hang out by the towers and handle runners.<br />
<br />
Kill the captains/generals/warlords last on each wave.<br />
<br />
We like to kill the spearmen to the west (toward velks) during the first wave (one group will mow them down, and first wave is numbingly easy) so we can engage the pops there earlier, but it's not necessary.<br />
<br />
No reason to bother with the MQ, feel free to run around and fight as the risk of death is pretty minimal.  If you lose, it will be due to runners, not because your force was wiped by giants.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
