		<div>You can't gate third wave, the levels are too high...Ring War is easily doable with a coordinated raid force of 36 people, our guild farms NToV (family guild) and we do Ring Wars with around 6-7 grps regularly, or we did as recently as a month or so ago.  Most of the reason for this is a rock solid strategy; we play it almost like a football game.  We engage in certain spots, we control the mobs completely (most are rootable).  Read somewhere once that a full ring war was done with about 15 people; I call BS on this one, think even with that mostly being root classes its still a lie, but who knows? /shrug.  Anyway, its a pretty simple encounter, keep KOS people away from the Dain, you can lose heroes quickly that way if you're not careful, and sure as HELL make sure everyone knows not to attack the Dain (lost an Eye of Narandi on my own ring war, I know its the crappiest loot but still)  At any rate, have fun with it, its one of my favorite encounters in the game, and distributing the loot afterward is fun, as you get 3 pretty darn nice loots (Crown, Choker, Faceguard)  Crown and Choker still stand somewhat highly on peoples' lists of great items today, even after PoP.  Have fun!</div>
