		<!-- message -->
		<div>From my experience, its nice to have a force of about 40.  We have never failed with 40+.  Success between 30 and 40 is spotty.  Less than 30 would take a truly well coordinated force that really knows where to stand.  Even with a capable force, expect to fail once learning where the waves spawn.<br />
<br />
No idea on whether someone else can start the war or not.  <br />
<br />
As someone else said, when you fail its generally because of a runner getting though.  This can happen on waves one and two, but is most likely to happen on wave 3 because they are very resistant and root/snare do not seem to work unless you are on top of the mob.  Also, remember to kill the boss of each wave LAST or you will start the timer on the next spawn.  Two spawns at once on the second or third waves is almost certain failure.</div>
		<!-- / message -->
	
		
		
		
		
		
	
